                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.51/208.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affairs at London</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-01-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The American bankers have been advised by Cooper that the Council of foreign
                    bondholders cannot consider any proposal unless submitted and approved by the
                    British Foreign Office. It is important that the agreement be approved promptly
                    by the Foreign Office. Copy of the agreement was sent with instructions of
                    January 7. In the meantime Cooper’s copy should be available to the Foreign
                    Office.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
